cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on named entity recognition (NER) using character-level language models (CLMs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the capabilities of CLMs, which are machine learning models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses NLP techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's main focus is on NER, which is a subfield of NLP, indicating that it could belong to cs.NE (Natural Language Processing). Finally, the paper discusses multilingual NER, which suggests it could belong to cs.CY (Computational Linguistics).
